<subSubSection id="C34FC1B6FFFDFFEAD3D3F0FB082CD40E" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEA923DFFFDFFEAD3D3F0FB0D21D757" blockId="1.[151,1437,1108,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFFDFFEAD3D3F0FB0D78D6A6" bold="true" box="[199,332,1180,1205]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Discussion.</emphasis>
The species was described based on an unspecified number of females from 
<collectingCountry id="F342D2ADFFFDFFEAD61DF0FB096BD6A6" box="[1289,1375,1180,1205]" name="Bolivia" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. The depository of its 
<typeStatus id="54EE2C9FFFFDFFEAD243F0A70DB3D6CB" box="[343,391,1216,1240]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">type</typeStatus>
material has remained unknown so far. A single female belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFFDFFEAD601F0A60CFBD6EE" authority="Stal, 1862" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Dystus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFFDFFEAD601F0A60955D6CB" box="[1301,1377,1217,1240]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Dystus</emphasis>
Stål, 
<number id="3D9D801AFFFDFFEAD383F0830CFBD6EE" box="[151,207,1252,1277]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" value="1862.0">1862</number>
</taxonomicName>
was found among unidentified scutellerids in 
<collectionCode id="ED440AF8FFFDFFEAD1CDF0830F2FD6EF" box="[729,795,1252,1276]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">SDEI</collectionCode>
. As it perfectly fits the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFFDFFEAD630F08209AFD6EF" authority="Stål, 1862" authorityName="Stål" authorityYear="1862" box="[1316,1435,1252,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Dystus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFFDFFEAD630F08209AFD6EF" box="[1316,1435,1252,1276]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">D. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it is from the 
<typeStatus id="54EE2C9FFFFDFFEAD248F16F0DB8D733" box="[348,396,1288,1312]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">type</typeStatus>
locality, there is no doubt that it is a 
<typeStatus id="54EE2C9FFFFDFFEAD03DF16F0FB4D733" box="[809,896,1288,1312]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">syntype</typeStatus>
and it is therefore designated as the 
<typeStatus id="54EE2C9FFFFDFFEAD603F160094AD733" box="[1303,1406,1287,1312]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFFDFFEAD383F14A0D3AD757" authority="Stål, 1862" authorityName="Stål" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,270,1324,1348]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Dystus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFFDFFEAD383F14A0D3AD757" box="[151,270,1324,1348]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">D. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA923DFFFDFFEAD3D3F1280D9ED7EB" blockId="1.[151,1437,1108,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">
The species was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFFDFFEAD14FF1360F52D77B" authority="Stal, 1862" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[603,870,1359,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Dystus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puberulus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFFDFFEAD14FF1360EDAD77B" box="[603,750,1360,1384]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">D. puberulus</emphasis>
Stål, 
<number id="3D9D801AFFFDFFEAD03AF1280F52D77B" box="[814,870,1359,1384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" value="1862.0">1862</number>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC4EFCCFFFDFFEAD085F128085DD77B" author="Schouteden" box="[913,1129,1359,1384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" refString="Schouteden, H. (1904) Heteroptera, fam. Pentatomidae, subfam. Scutellerinae. In: Wytsman, P. (Ed.), Genera Insectorum, 24, 1 - 98, pls. 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="1904">
Schouteden (
<number id="3D9D801AFFFDFFEAD730F1370855D77B" box="[1060,1121,1360,1384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" value="1904.0">1904</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
; we confirm the synonymy of the two species. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFFDFFEAD2E1F1120E75D79F" authority="Stål, 1862" authorityName="Stål" authorityYear="1862" box="[501,577,1397,1420]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Dystus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFFDFFEAD2E1F1120E75D79F" box="[501,577,1397,1420]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Dystus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently monotypic; a photo of the only included species was given by Eger 
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFFDFFEAD3C2F1FE0D26D7A3" box="[214,274,1432,1456]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number id="3D9D801AFFFDFFEAD230F1F00D55D7A3" box="[292,353,1431,1456]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" value="2015.0">2015</number>
), ink drawings and descriptions of the adult and all preimaginal stages as well as the genital capsule and parameres of the male were provided by Cervantes 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC4EFCCFFFDFFEAD07CF1DB083FD7C7" author="Peredo" box="[872,1035,1468,1493]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" refString="Cervantes-Peredo, L. (2004) Dystus puberulus Stal (Heteroptera: Scutelleridae) a shield bug associated with figs in Mexico. Florida Entomologist, 87 (4), 528 - 532. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1653 / 0015 - 4040 (2004) 087 [0528: DPSHSA] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2004">
Peredo (
<number id="3D9D801AFFFDFFEAD0D2F1DB0830D7C7" box="[966,1028,1468,1492]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The latter work also documents its host plant and life cycle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA923DFFFDFFEAD3D3F263082CD40E" blockId="1.[151,1437,1108,1565]" box="[199,1048,1540,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFFDFFEAD3D3F2630D48D40E" bold="true" box="[199,380,1540,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Current status.</emphasis>
Junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFFDFFEAD1C1F2620820D40E" authority="Stal, 1862" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[725,1044,1540,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Dystus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puberulus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFFDFFEAD1C1F2620FACD40F" box="[725,920,1540,1564]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Dystus puberulus</emphasis>
Stål, 
<number id="3D9D801AFFFDFFEAD0CCF2630820D40E" box="[984,1044,1540,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" value="1862.0">1862</number>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
